<SECTION>Recently shipped hardware

<ENTRY>shipped-4gb-seagate 4GB Seagate SCSI drive
William Gnadt <wgnadt@rri-usa.org> shipped a 4GB Seagate SCSI drive to
Phil Nelson <phil@netbsd.org> (the <a
href="../Ports/pc532/index.html">NetBSD/pc532 portmaster</a>), to
provide sufficient disk space for complete builds and tests of NetBSD
on the pc532. [19990511].

<ENTRY>shipped-sparc1+ Sun SPARC 1+
Brad Salai <bsalai@servtech.com> shipped a SPARC 1+ with either a
little or no memory to Steven Grunza <steven.grunza@dgms.com> to help
with work on sysinst and other projects for <a
href="../Ports/sparc/index.html">NetBSD/sparc</a>. [19990509].

<ENTRY>shipped-isa-interlan ISA Interlan ethernet cards
David Brownlee <abs@netbsd.org> shipped a couple of 8 bit NI5210/8
<jonathan@DSG.Stanford.EDU>, and Rafal Boni (rafal at mediaone dot
net), who are looking to work on a driver [19990423].

<ENTRY>shipped-sun3-80 Sun3/80 motherboard and RAM
David Brownlee <abs@netbsd.org> shipped a sun 3/80 motherboard with 4MB
RAM to Alex Barclay <alex@vsys.com> to help with his cache work on <a
href="../Ports/sun3/index.html">NetBSD/sun3</a> [1990422].

<ENTRY>shipped-pc532 PC532 for build lab
<a href="http://www.freebsd.org/~jkh/">Jordan K. Hubbard</a> shipped a PC532
to the build lab.

<ENTRY>many-others Many, many others
People have been contributing hardware to NetBSD developers since the start of
